    <string name="api_key_security_title">API Key Security Information</string>    
    <string name="api_key_security_explanation">**Your API Keys are stored securely.**\n\n
    **Encryption:**\n
    Your API keys are encrypted and stored securely on your device using Android\'s EncryptedSharedPreferences. This encryption uses the Android KeyStore system for maximum security.\n\n
    **Client-side only architecture:**\n
    All API requests are made directly from your device to the AI service. Your API keys are never sent to our servers or stored elsewhere.\n\n
    **Complete transparency:**\n
    You can view exactly how your API keys are handled in our open-source code at [https://github.com/Tomer-Barak/PostAngel](https://github.com/Tomer-Barak/PostAngel). The app code shows that API requests go directly to the API servers with your keys.\n\n
    **API keys usage:**\n
    Your keys are only used for:\n
    - Text generation with language model APIs\n
    - Image analysis with Vision models\n\n
    **Your data stays private:**\n
    Since we don\'t route your API requests through our servers, we never see your data or API key.</string>

